From 6045b93c4ef7a713c8f3d6837ca69f8e96b12bf1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Pickering <matthewtpickering@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Aug 2024 16:06:20 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Remove "install-includes: HsDirectoryConfig.h"

This header file is not supposed to be installed for users, users are
not supposed to use it. The file exists to be used interally (and this
is explained by the "include-dirs" field in the cabal file.

It seems likely that this removal was overlooked in
c87be9908023896a7f270bb076731ffba6c151b5
---
 directory.buildinfo | 1 -
 directory.cabal     | 1 -
 2 files changed, 2 deletions(-)
 delete mode 100644 directory.buildinfo

diff --git a/directory.buildinfo b/directory.buildinfo
deleted file mode 100644
index e19f7726..00000000
--- a/directory.buildinfo
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1 +0,0 @@
-install-includes: HsDirectoryConfig.h
diff --git a/directory.cabal b/directory.cabal
index af35f1d1..9921cfa1 100644
--- a/directory.cabal
+++ b/directory.cabal
@@ -28,7 +28,6 @@ extra-source-files:
     System/Directory/Internal/*.h
     configure
     configure.ac
-    directory.buildinfo
     tests/*.hs
     tests/util.inl
 
